        <abstract> 
<p>Response to ARW’s "Creation by law", especially the <hi rend="italic">Angraecum sesquipedale</hi> and the predicted Madagascar moth.</p> 
            <p>ARW’s argument on beauty strikes CD as good.</p> 
<p>Wishes ARW had made more clear the assumption of the reviewer [in <hi rend="italic">North Br. Rev.</hi>] that each variation is a strongly marked one.</p> 
            <p>The Duke of Argyll’s argument on beauty is not candid.</p>
        </abstract>
